  "prompt": "English Grammar: Is it 'Can you explain me?' or 'Could you explain me?'",
  "response": "Neither \"Can you explain me?\" nor \"Could you explain me?\" is correct if you intend to ask someone to clarify something to you. Instead, you should say:\n\n- \"Can you explain it to me?\"\n- \"Could you explain it to me?\"\n\nThe phrase \"explain me\" would imply explaining you as a person, which is not typically what is meant. The correct expressions include \"it to me\" or specifying what should be explained.",
